## Explain a Complex Bug You Faced and How You Fixed It

One complex issue involved inconsistent chart generation when users had limited test history. The analytics engine would fail when trying to generate trend lines with insufficient data points.

**Solution**:
1. Added data validation checks before chart generation
2. Implemented fallback mechanisms to show "insufficient data" messages
3. Created minimum data requirement thresholds for each chart type
4. Added graceful error handling that returns partial results when possible

This ensured users with limited history still received meaningful feedback without system crashes.

